<item>
            <title>[TIKA-113] Metadata (such as title) should not be part of content</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-113</link>
                <project id="12310631" key="TIKA">Tika</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Metadata (such as title)  is added in the content. In my opinion it would be preferable  that the toString () on the writer return only the content of the document and not metadata. The metadata  are already  stored in the metadata object&lt;br/&gt;
Rida.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
