                            <comment id="12560807" author="jukkaz" created="Sun, 20 Jan 2008 15:02:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think the SAX event stream should still contain selected metadata in the &amp;lt;head/&amp;gt; section. For example the current XHTMLContentHandler outputs the TITLE metadata field (if available) as the &amp;lt;title/&amp;gt; of the generated XML document.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Instead of changing that pattern, we should probably either change WriteOutContentHandler to only output content of the &amp;lt;body/&amp;gt; element or add a new ContentHandler utility class with that feature.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12560908" author="rbenjelloun" created="Mon, 21 Jan 2008 01:45:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1, I agree with Jukka suggestion.&lt;br/&gt;
Rida.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12569683" author="jukkaz" created="Sun, 17 Feb 2008 09:47:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A solution based on the current code is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Writer writer = ...;&lt;br/&gt;
    XPathParser xpath = new XPathParser(&quot;xhtml&quot;, &quot;http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml&quot;);&lt;br/&gt;
    ContentHandler handler = new MatchingContentHandler(&lt;br/&gt;
            new WriteOutContentHandler(writer),&lt;br/&gt;
            xpath.parse(&quot;/xhtml:html/xhtml:body//*&quot;));&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not sure if we should to codify that into a helper class or a method.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12587582" author="jukkaz" created="Thu, 10 Apr 2008 11:50:51 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Resolved in revision  646748 by implementing a BodyContentHandler class for getting just the XHTML body content.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
